<FILEID>AP-NR-07-05-88 2344EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>u i AM-GulfAttack     07-05 0137</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Gulf Attack,0141</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Iran Reportedly Raids Merchant Ship</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANAMA, Bahrain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iranian gunboats raided a merchant vessel
in the Strait of Hormuz in a predawn strike Wednesday and set it on
fire, said shipping executives based in the Persian Gulf.
   The executives identified the ship as the Atlantic Ocean and
said it had a Korean crew. They had no further details.
   The ship put out a distress signal at 2:30 a.m. Wednesday (6:30
p.m. EDT Tuesday), said the executives, who spoke on condition they
not be identified.
   The vessel reported a fire on board and asked for assistance.
   The attack, just three days after a U.S. warship shot down an
Iranian passenger jet, underscored Iran's determination to continue
the ``tanker war'' in the gulf to defeat Iraq, whom it has been
fighting since September 1980.
</TEXT>
