<1ST_LINE>u a AM-ChlorineFire     07-05 0172</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Chlorine Fire,0177</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>At Least 24 Taken To Hospital After Fire at Pool Company</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSON TOWNSHIP, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At least 24 firefighters and
emergency medical personnel were taken to hospitals Monday night
after a fire at a swimming pool company released chlorine into the
air, officials said.
   The blaze at Turmart Pool Co. began about 7:30 p.m. and was
declared under control before 10 p.m. About 150 firefighters
battled the fire at its height.
   Officials evacuated a few homes as a precaution but no
structures were threatened, including a nursing home about 1,000
feet away from the plant, said a fire dispatcher who would not give
his name.
   A nursing supervisor at Freehold Area Hospital said 20 people,
mostly firefighters, were brought to the hospital with coughing,
burning eyes and chest pains.
   Four firefighters were brought to Kimball Medical Center with
similar symptoms, nursing supervisor Elizabeth Fister said.
   ``They seem to be OK,'' Ms. Fister said.
   Firefighters had not yet determined a cause for the blaze, the
fire dispatcher said.
</TEXT>
