<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--TrainDerailment 1stLd-Writethru a0404 07-05 0161</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Train Derailment, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0404,0160</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Train Derailment Provides Holiday Feast For Birds</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Subs 4th graf, `Two cranes ...' and last graf to correct
upright to right.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LA GRANGE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A freight train derailment in this west
Chicago suburb was for the birds, police said.
   An Indiana Harbor Belt Railroad train heading for Blue Island
derailed at about 8 a.m. Monday, spewing tons of corn across the
tracks, Lt. Loren Clark said.
   ``There's corn all over,'' Clark said. ``The pigeons are having
a field day.''
   Two cranes and two bulldozers were working to right the six
railroad cars that tipped over following the derailment, police Lt.
Fred Goss said. Each car carried about 40 tons of grain.
   There were no injuries in the accident.
   By afternoon, four of the cars had been righted, but Goss said
crews today would continue to clean up the mess and fix about 300
to 400 feet of damaged track.
</TEXT>
