<1ST_LINE>r p PM-PoliticalQuotes     07-05 0189</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Political Quotes,200</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments from the presidential
campaign trail:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   
   GEORGE BUSH, saying U.S. policy will not change in the wake of
the downing of Iran Air Flight 655: ``Life goes on. Our mission
goes on and the world keeps turning.''
   
   JESSE JACKSON, giving an uncharacteristic ``no comment'' on his
Fourth of July meeting with Democratic nominee-to-be Michael
Dukakis: ``Our conversation is private, and should remain private.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, on the U.S. shooting down of the Iranian
civilian airliner: ``As long as this senseless war between Iran and
Iraq continues ... as long as we and the entire international
community fail to use our combined efforts to stop it, there will
be more tragedies, more heartaches and the ever-present risk of
more accidents in the (Persian) Gulf.''
   
   HAROLD BROOKS-BAKER, director of the British Burke's Peerage,
saying Vice President Bush has blood ties to all other European
royal families: ``Mr. Bush is without doubt connected to more great
royal families than any reigning head of state today except His
Serene Highness Franz Josef of Liechtenstein.''
</TEXT>
