<2ND_LINE>PM-Iran-US, 1st Ld-Writethru,a0516,0206</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Iran's Ambassador Says Retaliation Will Not Occur on U.S. Soil</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: LEADS with four grafs to CORRECT spelling of Mostafavi. Pick
up 5th pvs, `Asked how...'</NOTE>
<HEAD>With PM-Airliner Rdp, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iran's ambassador to West Germany
pledged today that his country will avenge a U.S. warship's downing
of an Iranian jetliner, but said retaliation will not occur on
American soil.
   ``We will not let this act go unanswered. We will give a direct
and clear response,'' said Ambassador Mehdi Ahary Mostafavi.
   Mostafavi was asked during a news conference if Iran would send
commandos to the United States to seek revenge for Sunday's downing
over the Persian Gulf of an Iran Air Airbus A300, whose 290
passengers and crew are all presumed dead.
   ``It was the Americans who came into our region, and we have the
right to defend ourselves there. We will not reverse the
situation,'' Mostafavi responded.
   Asked how Iran would reply to Sunday's disaster, he said, ``We
will give our answer to the aggressor himself.''
   The United States said officers aboard the warship mistook the
A300 for an Iranian F-14 fighter and shot it down after it failed
to respond to seven warnings.
</TEXT>
