<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Pope-Iran     07-05 0184</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Pope-Iran,0187</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pope Sends Telegram Of Condolence To Iran</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pope John Paul II said today he was ``deeply
distressed'' over the downing of an Iranian airliner and urged that
steps be taken to prevent such an incident from occurring again.
   In a telegram sent in his name by Vatican Secretary of State
Cardinal Agostino Casaroli, the pope expressed his condolences to
Iranian officials and families of those killed when the U.S.
cruiser Vincennes shot down the Iranian Airbus over the Persian
Gulf on Sunday. Iran said all 290 people aboard were killed.
   ``Deeply distressed by the tragedy that provoked the death of so
many passengers and crew members of a civilian Iranian plane, the
pope ... asks you to express his deepest condolences to the Iranian
authorities, and through them, to the families in mourning,'' said
the telegram, addressed to the Holy See's ambassador in Tehran.
   The pope urged ``that everything is done so that similar
tragedies are not repeated and that all efforts are made so that
the region rediscovers the peace to which all the world aspires.''
