<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Bomb Explodes,0164</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Student In Fair Condition After Explosion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TULSA, Okla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Tulsa University student said he was
making holiday fireworks when material he was using exploded in an
art studio, blowing off part of his hand.
   Morris David Roth, 21, was hospitalized in fair condition after
the explosion Sunday blew off his left thumb and parts of his left
index and middle fingers, authorities said.
   ``I'm not out to hurt anyone,'' Roth said Monday. ``I'm
basically a loner pyrotechnics hobbyist. I don't have the money to
spend on fireworks so I make my own.''
   However, Fire Marshal Jim Pilkington said the 20 pounds of
explosives investigators recovered from the university art studio
were ``capable of considerable damage to structures and people.''
   Roth, who said he learned to make bombs from books, said he had
planned to explode several bombs in a field to celebrate the Fourth
of July.
   No charges had been filed by this morning.
</TEXT>
