<HEAD>Single-Engine Plane Hits House; Pilot in Critical Condition</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLEARWATER, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A single-engine plane slammed into a
house early today, critically injuring the pilot, but three people
in the house apparently escaped serious injury, the Pinellas County
Sheriff's Office reported.
   The plane crashed at about 6:20 a.m. northeast of the Clearwater
Executive Air Park, said Sgt. William Logan. ``The fire there was
probably from fuel from the aircraft but it is under control,''
Logan said.
   Logan described injuries to the occupants of the house as minor.
   The pilot was taken to Bayfront Medical Center in St.
Petersburg, where he was listed in critical condition suffering
from burns, said Beth Marshall, director of the hospital's
emergency trauma services. The pilot's identity was not released by
the hospital.
