<HEAD>Trooper Shoots Trucker In Head After 65-Mile Chase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A truck driver ran through a tollgate
and tried to ram several patrol cars during a 65-mile chase on
Interstate 70 before a trooper shot him in the head, authorities
said.
   David W. Cole, 28, of Providence, Ky., was in critical condition
today. No one else was injured, said Trooper Janet Trammell.
   Officials in Kansas, where the chase began, said Cole had been
clocked speeding in his empty tractor-trailer.
   ``The truck weaved from shoulder to shoulder and on several
occasions tried to strike the patrol cars,'' said Trammell.
   Cole drove through a roadblock at about 60 mph, Trammell said.
Police then fired at the truck and hit a left rear tire. Cole still
refused to stop, she said. A few miles away, a trooper shot Cole in
the head, Trammell said.
   Cole's brother, a passenger, pulled the vehicle off the road and
stopped.
