Anthony Earl and Kohl in the September primary race and was tied
with Edward Garvey for third place. Wisconsin Secretary of State
Douglas LaFollette was in fourth.
   The candidates are trying to win the seat being vacated by
Democratic Sen. William Proxmire, who announced last year he would
retire.
   If Moody decides to seek re-election to his 5th District seat,
he must file by July 12.
