on Tuesday. Thick clouds of smoke billowed from the shantytown as
Mousa's gunners, entrenched in Syrian-controlled hills above
Beirut, opened up with artillery, mortars and rockets.
   The fighting flared Monday, shattering a lull after the fall of
the nearby Chatilla camp to Mousa's men on June 27.
   Police said 35 mortar rounds hit the four-story Haifa Hospital
on Tuesday. The only surgeon in the camp, two nurses and a general
practioner left the shantytown around noon, during a short break in
the fighting.
   Police said nine seriously wounded Palestinian r Rdp Bjt
