<HEAD>Ford Announces Probe Price Increases Averaging $200</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. has raised prices of its
Probe models an average of about $200, the company said Tuesday.
   The increases took effect Friday. The Probe was introduced in
May. The two-door coupes are designed by Ford, jointly engineered
by Ford and Mazda Motor Corp. and manufactured for Ford at Mazda's
plant at Flat Rock.
