<HEAD>Columbia Gas System Negotiating to Sell Partial Interest in LNG
Unit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Columbia Gas System Inc. announced
Tuesday it is negotiating to sell a 50 percent interest in its
subsidiary, Columbia LNG Corp., to Shell Oil Co. of Houston.
   Columbia said if the negotiations are successful, the parties
expect to form a joint venture to purchase liquefied natural gas
supplies and to market the LNG regasified at a terminal Columbia
LNG owns at Cove Point, Md.
   The terminal has the capacity to send out 1 billion cubic feet
of gas daily.
   Columbia said the terminal on the Chesapeake Bay is a
strategically located entry point to major eastern energy markets
through its pipeline access to interstate transmission systems.
