<2ND_LINE>BC-Weekly Steel,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Steel Output Rose 0.8 Percent in Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production rose to 1.834 million tons in
the week ended July 2, an increase of 0.8 percent from the previous
week's 1.819 million tons, the American Iron and Steel Institute
reported Tuesday.
   The industry's production amounted to 82.2 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 84.9 percent in the previous week.
The trade group said it had increased the steelmaking capacity
figure it is using for the third quarter by 100,000 tons to an
annual rate of 28 million tons.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
50.923 million net tons, an increase of 21.8 percent from the
41.800 million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 90.3 percent of capacity,
compared with 74.3 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended July 2: Northeast
Coast, 281,000; Pittsburgh, 200,000; Youngstown, 120,000; Lake
Erie, 152,000; Detroit, 144,000; Chicago, 446,000; Midwest,
189,000; Southern, 208,000; and Western, 94,000.
</TEXT>
