<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Medserv-Soviets     07-05 0209</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Medserv-Soviets,0216</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Health Services Company Signs Contract with Soviet Union</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Medserv Corp., a diversified health
services company, said Tuesday it has reached separate agreements
to help set up a neonatal clinic in Moscow and a dental laboratory
in the Ukraine.
   The company said it expects to sign contracts for the two
ventures in September, and estimated they will be worth a total of
about $150 million.
   Under a $140 million agreement with All Union Scientific
Research Center in Moscow, Medserv will design, construct, equip
and train technical staff for a new 160-unit neonatal facility. The
facility, which will be part of the Institute for Mother and Child,
will treat children under age 1.
   Medserv also signed a letter of intent with Licensintorg and the
Central Dental Scientific Institute to provide equipment, raw
materials, training and technology for production of filling
composite materials at a dental manufacturing facility in the
Ukraine. That contract will be worth about $10 million, Medserv
said.
   Medserv has three operating subsidiaries: Primedica, which
manages hospital-based cardiopulmonary and respiratory therapy
units, manages neonatal care units and provides medical equipment
and homecare services; the Dental Services Group, a network of
dental laboratories; and Medvet, which is in the field of
veterinary pathology.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
